<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figures 4 - 6. Anaphes brevis. 4 head + base of antennae 5 antenna, outer surface 6 antenna, inner surface. Note difference in fl 4 and cross striations on inner surface of scape (striations very faint and more longitudinal on outer surface). Scale bars: 200 μm." , "Figures 2, 3. Anaphes brevis, head. 2 anterior 3 posterior. Scale bars: 100 μm." , "Figures 7 - 9. Anaphes brevis. 7 wings (see text for discussion) 8 body, dorsal 9 with frenum-gaster internal (more ventral) to show mesofurca and ovipositor through gaster; dashed line indicates anterior extension of ovipositor. Scale bars: 200 μm." , "Figures 10, 11. Anaphes brevis, body, lateral. 10 outer surface 11 median view of gaster showing ovipositor. Scale bars: 200 μm." , "Figure 1. Anaphes brevis, neotype, habitus. Scale bar: 500 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199688" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199692" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199687" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199690" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/199691" .

